cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the development of a large-scale neural language model for generating interactive suggestions in Gmail. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the system involves retrieving relevant suggestions based on the user's input. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of state-of-the-art machine learning techniques for language model training. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the system involves the use of AI to assist users in writing emails. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the system aims to improve the user experience in writing emails by reducing repetitive typing.
